# Change TFE Color Scheme

This guide shows how to customize colors in TFE.

## Location: styles.go

All color definitions are in `styles.go`. Here's the default color scheme:

```go
var (
    titleStyle = lipgloss.NewStyle().
        Foreground(lipgloss.Color("39")).  // Cyan title
        Bold(true)

    pathStyle = lipgloss.NewStyle().
        Foreground(lipgloss.Color("245"))  // Gray path

    selectedStyle = lipgloss.NewStyle().
        Background(lipgloss.Color("39")).  // Cyan highlight
        Foreground(lipgloss.Color("0")).   // Black text
        Bold(true)

    folderStyle = lipgloss.NewStyle().
        Foreground(lipgloss.Color("39"))   // Cyan folders

    fileStyle = lipgloss.NewStyle().
        Foreground(lipgloss.Color("252"))  // Light gray files
)
```

## Color Codes Reference

Common Lipgloss colors (256-color palette):

```
Grays:    232 (black) → 255 (white)
Blues:    17, 18, 19, 20, 21 (dark → bright)
Cyans:    23, 24, 25, 26, 27, 37, 38, 39
Greens:   22, 28, 34, 40, 46, 76, 82, 118
Yellows:  58, 100, 142, 184, 220, 226
Oranges:  166, 172, 178, 208, 214, 220
Reds:     52, 88, 124, 160, 196
Purples:  53, 54, 55, 56, 57, 91, 92, 93
```

Full palette: https://www.ditig.com/256-colors-cheat-sheet

